main event: An unidentified flying object was tracked on radar near Cape Canaveral, Florida on April 11, 1961.
interesting points: The radar detected the object flying at an altitude of approximately 10,000 to 15,000 feet for 15 minutes,Three experienced observers reported seeing the object orbiting 6 or 7 times while moving between 150 and 600 knots,The estimates of the object's height varied among the observers, with some saying it was very low and others stating it was very high,Despite multiple radar tracking attempts, there was no visual sighting or identification of the object,The incident was concluded to have insufficient data for a definitive explanation.
